The paper discusses the topic of knowledge distillation, which is a popular technique in machine learning and deep learning. The paper specifically focuses on the relationship between knowledge distillation and label smoothing regularization, and proposes a novel framework called Teacher-free Knowledge Distillation (Tf-KD). Given this, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
